All Classes

Class Summary
Class Description
ArmyUnit
ArmyUnit contains infantry and tanks, which have different parameters values such as maxHp, hp, maxAmmo, ammo, team.
Base
Base is a stationary Unit.
ConsoleApp
optional console interface
Field
Field is a object that can store 1 armyUnit and 1 neutralUnit.
MainApp
main class for application
Map
Creates 2D array of fields
MovingBase
Moving base moves on the map and delivers supplies to ArmyUnits (if has any usesLeft).
MovingUnit
abstract class for ArmyUnit and MovingBase
sceneMainController
processes user interaction with main menu
sceneOptionsController
processes user options choices.
sceneParamsController
processes user changes of simulation parameters
sceneProgressController
displays information after simulation finishes
Simulation
Simulation back-end logic
SimulationConstants
Stores custom constants for each type of unit those values are not available to be changed during simulation startup
Supplies
Stores data about hp and ammo of each ArmyUnit.
Trap
Traps are spawned at the start of the simulation.
Unit
Base class for all the Units.
UnitCreator
Creates list of Units to manage them better
